content:
Create a remote connection using the NetSuite connector to sync data from NetSuite to CRM Analytics.

To create a new connection:

On the Data Manager Connections tab, click New Connection.
Click the name of the connector, and click Next.
Enter the connector settings:
Connection Name: Identifies the connections
Developer Name: API name for the connection (no spaces)
Description: Description
Consumer Secret: Client password associated with the NetSuite account
Consumer Key: Client key associated with the NetSuite account
Account ID: NetSuite account ID
Rest Domain: Rest domain name in the format https://<Rest Domain Name>.netsuite.com
Token ID: Token ID for the access token generated in NetSuite
Token Secret: Token secret for the access token generated in NetSuite

When working with the Netsuite connector:

* Connected object names must start with a letter and contain only letters, digits, or underscores.
* This connector can sync up to 100,000 rows or 500 MB per object.
* Use English alphanumeric characters A-Z, a-z, and 1-9 in object names.

To upgrade to the new codebase version of this connector, see the Summer '21 release note.
title: Connecting NetSuite to CRM Analytics
